Clonmacnoise was then clearly “in the ecclesiastical province of Tuam—was small, con- sisting of only twelve homes, built of rushes and mud, and thatched with straw.’' According to the report‚ ‘⁶ the cathedral was then in ruins—ecclesiam cathedralem esse dirutam. Its sacristy, too, was small ; but its belsry had two bells. The Holy Sacrifice was seldom offered up. and the whole revenue of the See amounted to only thirty-three crowns. '
